-- Ontario Teachers’ Pension Plan to Buy Busy Bees Nurserys
-- B y   K i e l   P o r t e r
-- 2013-10-31T08:20:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-31/ontario-teachers-pension-plan-to-buy-busy-bees-nurserys.html
The Ontario Teachers’ Pension Plan
has agreed to buy U.K. childcare provider for an undisclosed
sum, according to a joint e-mailed statement today.
*Investment made by private equity division, Teachers’ Private
Capital, TPC: statement
*Founded in 1983, Busy Bees operates 213 nurseries: statement
*TPC plans to develop new locations and acquire other facilities
head of Teachers’ London office Jo Taylor says  To contact the reporter on this story:
